The paper discusses the use of computer vision techniques for controlling the orientation of an assistive robotic device for grasping objects. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also focuses on off-loading low-level control from the end-user, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The algorithm used for object detection and orientation computation involves machine learning techniques, which falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
